                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herdliska</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 8, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Herdliska refers to Mr. Adee’s telegram of August 29 respecting withdrawal
                    of foreign contingents from Pekin and reports that the foreign office entertains
                    well-founded hope that agreement will be arrived at between cooperating powers
                    as to date thereof, whereby this question will find satisfactory solution. He
                    adds that the Austrian charge had left Pekin and arrived at Taku at time of the
                    communication of Mr. Hay’s telegram.)</p>
            </div>
